  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Freelance Business Development Consultant (China Market – Commission Based)",
  "description": "<h3> Job Description</h3><p>We are a boutique <strong>Singapore accounting & corporate secretarial firm</strong> seeking a <strong>Freelance Business Development Consultant</strong> to introduce <strong>China-based clients</strong> looking to set up companies in Singapore.</p><p>This is a <strong>commission-based freelance role</strong>, ideal for individuals with strong China market networks and experience working with Chinese entrepreneurs or investors.</p><h3>🔹 Key Responsibilities</h3><ul><li><p>Introduce China-based clients interested in:</p><ul><li><p>Singapore company incorporation</p></li><li><p>Accounting, tax & corporate secretarial services</p></li></ul></li><li><p>Act as a bridge between China clients and our Singapore firm</p></li><li><p>Assist in preliminary discussions and client introductions</p></li></ul><h3>🔹 Requirements</h3><ul><li><p>Strong familiarity with the <strong>China market</strong></p></li><li><p>Existing network of China-based business owners or investors</p></li><li><p>Experience in:</p><ul><li><p>Business development, consulting, or cross-border services</p></li></ul></li><li><p>Fluent in <strong>Mandarin</strong> (spoken & written)</p></li><li><p>Self-motivated and results-driven</p></li></ul><h3>🔹 Remuneration</h3><ul><li><p><strong>Commission-based only</strong></p></li><li><p>Competitive commission for each successful deal</p></li><li><p>Commission payable upon client signing and payment received</p></li><li><p>No cap on earnings</p></li></ul><h3>🔹 Work Arrangement</h3><ul><li><p>Freelance / independent contractor</p></li><li><p>Remote and flexible</p></li><li><p>No fixed working hours</p></li></ul><h3>🔹 Who should apply</h3><p>This role is suitable for:</p><ul><li><p>Freelance consultants</p></li><li><p>Former bankers, relationship managers, or agents</p></li><li><p>Individuals with strong China-Singapore business connections</p></li></ul>",
